Here's a list of essential Docker commands, grouped by functionality:

1. Container Management:
   ```
   docker run       # Create and start a new container
   docker start     # Start an existing container
   docker stop      # Stop a running container
   docker restart   # Restart a container
   docker pause     # Pause a running container
   docker unpause   # Unpause a paused container
   docker rm        # Remove a container
   docker exec      # Execute a command in a running container
   docker attach    # Attach to a running container
   docker logs      # Fetch the logs of a container
   docker inspect   # Display detailed information on a container
   docker ps        # List running containers
   docker ps -a     # List all containers (including stopped)
   ```

2. Image Management:
   ```
   docker pull      # Pull an image from a registry
   docker push      # Push an image to a registry
   docker build     # Build an image from a Dockerfile
   docker images    # List images
   docker rmi       # Remove an image
   docker tag       # Create a tag for an image
   docker save      # Save an image to a tar archive
   docker load      # Load an image from a tar archive
   docker import    # Import the contents from a tarball to create an image
   ```

3. Network Management:
   ```
   docker network create    # Create a network
   docker network connect   # Connect a container to a network
   docker network disconnect # Disconnect a container from a network
   docker network ls        # List networks
   docker network rm        # Remove a network
   docker network inspect   # Display detailed information on a network
   ```

4. Volume Management:
   ```
   docker volume create    # Create a volume
   docker volume ls        # List volumes
   docker volume rm        # Remove a volume
   docker volume inspect   # Display detailed information on a volume
   ```

5. System & Docker Daemon:
   ```
   docker info      # Display system-wide information
   docker version   # Show the Docker version information
   docker events    # Get real time events from the server
   docker system df # Show docker disk usage
   docker system prune # Remove unused data
   ```

6. Docker Compose:
   ```
   docker-compose up     # Create and start containers
   docker-compose down   # Stop and remove containers, networks, images, and volumes
   docker-compose start  # Start services
   docker-compose stop   # Stop services
   docker-compose build  # Build or rebuild services
   docker-compose logs   # View output from containers
   ```

7. Docker Swarm:
   ```
   docker swarm init     # Initialize a swarm
   docker swarm join     # Join a swarm as a node or manager
   docker swarm leave    # Leave the swarm
   docker service create # Create a new service
   docker service ls     # List services
   docker service rm     # Remove a service

  To access a docker container on a server remotely from your local machine, kindly run this command 
  export DOCKER_HOST="ssh://root@server publicIP"
  
  
